longer, that it will be his death, wherefore we most humbly
intreat your Worship, that he may be bayled foorth, you
shall haue sufficient Citizens and good Subsedie men to bee
bound for his apparance at the next sisses, to answere what 
soeuer can be laid against him. The good Iustice noting
their speech, and therewithall their persons, makes this
